<code>/home/xiaoqingguo/Rongkun/code/Hyper-Tell</code>.</p>\\\\n  </header>\\\\n\\\\n  <section>\\\\n    <h2>Summary</h2>\\\\n    <p>Executed P4 using path B for the effective VoxTell v1.1 checkpoint profile: keep <code>num_heads=32</code>. This preserves Body-Tell mask-fusion capacity and matches the shipped VoxTell v1.1 predictor/checkpoint projection dimensions found by SP-A.P0, while recording the source-default <code>num_heads=1</code> case as a conditional P6 skip policy.</p>\\\\n    <p>Renamed projection modules to VoxTell-compatible state-dict names, changed bottleneck token layout to VoxTell's <code>B,C,D,H,W -&gt; B,H,W,D,C -&gt; H*W*D,B,C</code> path, and added non-cubic shape coverage to catch D/H/W swaps.</p>\\\\n  </section>\\\\n\\\\n  <section>\\\\n    <h2>Files Changed</h2>\\\\n    <table>\\\\n      <thead><tr><th>Path</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>\\\\n      <tbody>\\\\n        <tr><td><code>Body-Tell/body_tell/models/voxtell_body_model.py</code></td><td>Renamed <code>project_visual_embed</code> to <code>project_bottleneck_embed</code>, renamed <code>mask_projections</code> to <code>project_to_decoder_channels</code>, kept <code>num_heads=32</code>, and switched bottleneck memory flattening to H/W/D order.</td></tr>\\\\n        <tr><td><code>Body-Tell/tests/test_model_shapes.py</code></td><td>Added projection-name/state-dict checks, path-B projection dimension checks, and a non-cubic <code>32 x 64 x 96</code> forward test proving output axes stay <code>D,H,W</code>.</td></tr>\\\\n        <tr><td><code>Body-Tell/scripts/audit_voxtell_alignment.py</code></td><td>Updated current Body-Tell projection reporting to the new <code>project_to_decoder_channels</code> prefix.</td></tr>\\\\n        <tr><td><code>Body-Tell/scripts/parameter_audit.py</code></td><td>Updated subtree probes for the new projection and decoder module names.</td></tr>\\\\n        <tr><td><code>Body-Tell/reports/26-05-24/runs/SP-A.P4/audit_projection_after_p4.html</code></td><td>Generated HTML audit artifact showing aligned projection dimensions and P6 whitelist input.</td></tr>\\\\n        <tr><td><code>Body-Tell/reports/26-05-24/runs/SP-A.P4/RESULT.html</code></td><td>This result report.</td></tr>\\\\n      </tbody>\\\\n    </table>\\\\n    <p class=\\\\\\\"meta\\\\\\\">No edits were made to <code>Body-Tell/reports/26-05-24/lead.html</code> or <code>Body-Tell/reports/26-05-24/workflow_manifest.yaml</code>. Those files were already modified in the worktree before this task.</p>\\\\n  </section>\\\\n\\\\n  <section>\\\\n    <h2>Verification</h2>\\\\n    <h3>Requested shape suite</h3>\\\\n    <pre><code>conda run -n voxtell python -m pytest Body-Tell/tests/test_model_shapes.py\\\\n\\\\ncollected 8 items\\\\nBody-Tell/tests/test_model_shapes.py ........                            [100%]\\\\n8 passed in 16.51s</code></pre>\\\\n\\\\n    <h3>Projection / whitelist audit artifact</h3>\\\\n    <pre><code>conda run -n voxtell python Body-Tell/scripts/audit_voxtell_alignment.py \\\\\\\\\\\\n  --config Body-Tell/configs/phase1_voxtell_aligned.yaml \\\\\\\\\\\\n  --skip-state-dict-compare \\\\\\\\\\\\n  --html-output Body-Tell/reports/26-05-24/runs/SP-A.P4/audit_projection_after_p4.html\\\\n\\\\nBody-Tell current: num_heads=32, fused projection stages=5\\\\nproject_to_decoder_channels outputs: [32, 2048, 4096, 8192, 10240]\\\\nVoxTell source default: num_heads=1, outputs [32, 64, 128, 256, 320]\\\\nVoxTell v1.1 checkpoint inferred num_heads=32, outputs [32, 2048, 4096, 8192, 10240]\\\\nP6 required skip: pos_embed\\\\nP6 conditional skip: project_to_decoder_channels.[1-4].*, decoder.transpconvs.[1-4].*, decoder.seg_layers.* only for a source-default num_heads=1 checkpoint\\\\nP6 note: do not skip projection or mask-fusion keys for the shipped v1.1 checkpoint due to num_heads</code></pre>\\\\n\\\\n    <h3>Compile and whitespace checks</h3>\\\\n    <pre><code>conda run -n voxtell python -m py_compile \\\\\\\\\\\\n  Body-Tell/body_tell/models/voxtell_body_mod